sections.heading: Overview
content:
Patsy Catsos, MS, RD, is a registered dietitian in Portland, Maine. She
provides nutrition counseling to clients with GI disorders and food
sensitivities and helps them with day-to-day management of symptoms through
diet and nutrition.

Catsos was educated at Cornell University (BS), Boston University (MS) and
Boston's Beth Israel Hospital. She is a member of the American Dietetic
Association and is president-elect of the Maine Dietetic Association.

Catsos is an adjunct faculty member at Andover College. She is the author of
the 2009 book, IBS -- Free at Last!
